    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Input inside the label is wrong on both semantical and W3c aspect.\n\nHmm, that's how Bootstrap does it for checkbox/radio. Wrapping an input in a label works the same as linking them through `for`/`id`, but this can actually be really helpful when styling.\n\n> Your proposition break the logic (User just added tittle of his facets, he won't understand why labels are not supported for a simple select)+ it's made to be easy so if I have to read the doc to make a valid markup, it's not cool.\n\nOh ok, you mean we should provide the API directly in the widget to add a label, to stay consistent with the fact that we already provide a way to add headers. Sorry, I did not get that. But yeah, that could be a nice improvement.\n",
