    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "But still... I'm not confortable with adding too many markup from the widget. If I take the Bootstrap example of doing selects in form this is:\n\n``` html\n<div class=\"form-group\">\n      <label for=\"selector\">Select menu</label>\n      <select id=\"selector\" class=\"form-control\">\n        <option>Option</option>\n      </select>\n</div>\n```\n\nWhich will translate in instantsearch to\n\n``` html\n<div class=\"form-group\">\n  <label for=\"selector\">Select menu</label>\n  <div id=\"selector-menu\"></div>\n</div>\n```\n\n``` javascript\nsearch.addWidget(\n  instantsearch.widgets.hitsPerPageSelector({\n    container: '#selector-menu',\n    options: [{},{}, ...],\n    selectId: 'selector',\n    cssClasses: {\n      root: 'form-control'\n    }\n  })\n);\n```\n\nI've only added the `selectId` option, that should add an `id` to the `select`, so it is correctly bound to the `label`. I don't think we should wrap the `select` in a `label` from the widget (not anybody would want a wrapped element). I'm not sure we should automatically add a label before the select (users not using Bootstrap might want it somewhere else, or wrapped in their own div).\n",
    "created_at": "2015-11-16T09:58:42Z",
