  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Just had an idea: what about imitating what's been done with HTML?\nWe don't want a hard-coded `<label>` inside each widget, but we could have a generic `label` widget that is given a reference to the widget it relates to using a `for` option/prop.\n\nWe should then have a way to synchronize the `display: none` (and the name/id for its real `for` attribute) between the widget and its label?\n\nSomething along those lines:\n\n``` javascript\nlet sortSelector = instantsearch.widgets.sortBySelector(...);\nsearch.addWidget(instantsearch.widgets.label({ container: '#sortby-wrapper', for: sortSelector }))\nsearch.addWidget(sortSelector);\n```\n\nWould that work?\n",
